# Implementation Plan - Module 2: Authentication & User Management

This plan outlines the design and implementation for Module 2: Authentication & User Management of the PLACE@ASET platform. It spans the database schema migrations, backend API routes, services, middleware, security practices, and a responsive frontend with auth pages and context.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Dual Token Mechanism**: We will implement HttpOnly Secure Cookies for storing the `refresh_token` to protect against XSS-based token theft, while the `access_token` will be returned in the JSON payload (to be kept in-memory by the frontend client) or as an authorization header.
> - **Role Syncing**: We will sync Supabase Auth's user role metadata with our public schema `user_roles` table. The `role` column in `users` will serve as the cached role, while the `user_roles` junction table will be the source of truth for role and permission checks.

## Open Questions

- None at the moment. We will proceed with implementing TypeScript on the backend and leveraging standard JSX on the frontend to keep it aligned with Next.js 14 App Router conventions.

